OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,423,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1772565072
OL,3,C'Stupid and childish' man drove 18-
OL,4,Ctonne coach into ex's bedroom window
OL,6,FAnderson then left the area but was
OL,7,Farrested later, charged and admitted
OL,8,Fthe offences at the earliest
OL,9,Fopportunity.
OL,11,FGlenn Reardon, defending, said
OL,12,FAnderson's intention was to cause
OL,13,Fembarrassment to his ex-partner.
OL,15,FAnderson had no previous convictions
OL,16,Fand he was struggling with his mental
OL,17,Fhealth at the time, the court heard.
OL,19,FMr Reardon said: "He does have a deep
OL,20,Fregret for his actions."
OL,26,@{D@ROU|D@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/7
